projectDesc.p: ParlaMint is a project that aims to (1) create a multilingual set of comparable corpora of parliamentary proceedings uniformly encoded according to the ParlaMint encoding guidelines, covering the period from 2015 to mid-2022; (2) add linguistic annotations to the corpora and machine-translate them to English; (3) make the corpora available through concordancers; and (4) build use cases in Political Sciences and Digital Humanities based on the corpus data.

prefixDef.p: Private URIs with this prefix point to aligned source elements of the MTed corpus.

div.head: Quinta-feira, 23 de março de 2017 I Série — Número 66
XIII LEGISLATURA 2.ª SESSÃO LEGISLATIVA (2016-2017)
div.note: Chairman: H.E. Mr. Eduardo Luís Barreto Ferro Rodrigues
Secretaries: Ex.mos Sr. Duarte Rogério Matos Ventura Pacheco Idália Maria Marques Salvador Serrano Carlos Bivar Branco de Penha Monteiro Sandra Maria Pereira Pontedeira

SUMMARY The President declared the meeting open at 3 p.m. and 6 minutes. The entry into the Bureau of draft laws Nos 459 to 462/XIII (2a) of draft Regiment No 1/XIII (2a) and draft resolutions Nos 741 to 755, 757 to 760 and 762/XIII (2a). An opinion of the Ethics Subcommittee of the Committee on Constitutional Affairs, Rights, Freedoms and Guarantees was adopted on the waiver of the mandate of a PSD Member and his replacement. Under Article 224(2)(b) of the Rules of Procedure, the 15th-year debate took place with the Prime Minister (António Costa), who answered the questions put by Mr Assumption Cristas (CDS-PP), Mr Luís Montenegro (PSD), Mr Júlia Rodrigues and Mr Gabriela Canavilhas (PS), Mr Catarina Martins (BE), Mr Jerónimo de Sousa (PCP), Mr Heloísa Apolónia (Os Verdes) — these last three speakers also expressed concern about the recent events in the British Parliament — and Mr André Silva (PAN). The President closed the meeting for 17 hours and 1 minute.
